 and Derivatives condenses more than 15 years of dedicated coverage of inflation markets. It provides investors, issuers and policy makers with all the relevant tools to navigate inflation markets, starting with the nuts and bolts of consumer price indices, forwards, carry and trading strategies, to advanced topics like seasonality adjustments and the use of inflation options. With its many illustrative graphs and tabulated data, this exceptional book will benefit traders, corporate treasury departments, fixed income investors, insurance companies and pension funds executives.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aDerivate. 4aInflationsindexierte Anleihe. 4aOptionen. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Banks & Banking.2bisacsh  aInflation Forecast.  aInflation Options.  aInflation Products.  aInflation Swaps.  aInflation-linked Bonds.1 aLeister, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRieger, Christoph, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2022 Englishz978311099282308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2022z9783110992922oZDB-23-DBV0 cEPUBz97831107874740 cprintz978311078737540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311078742940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110787429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110787429/original  a978-3-11-099282-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2022 Englishb2022